column5: Was converting the old vhs videos to dvds when I came across an old fishing video from a few years back. I put it on a Myspace account for better quality but it has to buffer a bit. MySpace won't play anything with songs that have been copyrighted (example: eye of the tiger(pike)) So don't waste the time uploading, The same goes for facebook. Which is too bad as the quality of videos on these site are much better then youtube. Iceguys Blast from the past
I was sitting on the edge of my seat and I didn't know what was going to happen!  Thanks for posting.
nice job! Try vimeo.com if you want high quality sound and video!
Nice fish - I didn't realize you knew Ed O'Neill.
Great vid.  I was a couple lakes over camped on Red Cedar Lake that same day.  Part of a 100km canoe loop in the area.  Wished we had those kinda fish on the line.
I like what I'm seeing with this site.  Hey Rod I fish with Al bundy all the time. "ahh Peg not tonight"
Nice job.....I can hardly wait to get out there!!!
Cool video.  I like that it was black and white too.  Joey
Nice Trout.  I really enjoy your video reports.
Nice laker !!!! great video man,keep up the hard work
